  "text": "My chapter at Kiwi.com is coming to an end, as my role was impacted by the recent company-wide layoffs. It was an amazing 9.5 years 💚\n\nDuring this time, I had the opportunity to grow across multiple roles and teams and work on different parts of the product. All of this shaped how I think about quality, frontend development, and collaboration. But most importantly, I met incredible people I can now call friends.\n\nAfter such a long journey, I’m taking a moment to recharge so I can move forward with renewed motivation and fresh energy. I’m now officially open to new opportunities.\n\n👩🏻‍💻 Roles I’m interested in:\n • Frontend Development\n • QA / SDET / Test Automation (Cypress / Playwright)\n\n📍 Location: Brno or remote\n 📅 Start date: March / April\n\nIf you’re hiring or know someone I should connect with, I’d truly appreciate the support. Thank you 🙏🏻\n\n#OpenToWork",
